   Mediterranean Seeds; Zera im Gedera; Int Soc Hort Sci Working Grp
   Curcurbitaceae},
Abstract = {Four Cucumis species (C. sativus, C. melo, C. metuliferus, C. zeyheri)
   were used in embryo-culture experiments. Embryos were excised from
   unripe fruits, one, two and three weeks after self-pollination. There
   were improved in vitro culture conditions. The most suitable conditions
   for the culture of Cucumis spp. embryos was with a medium with lower
   concentration of sucrose and growth regulators, and in the light. Plants
   were regenerated from immature embryos isolated two weeks after
   self-pollination for C. sativus and C. melo and three weeks after
   self-pollination for the other species. In general, embryo cultures of
   C. sativus and C. melo were more successful than the wild Cucumis spp.
   Plants of C. sativus were also obtained from immature seeds isolated one
   week after self-pollination.},
